HEADWORD: Water souchy
<hw>Wa"ter souch`y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Cookery)</fld> <def>A dish
consisting of small fish stewed and served in a little water.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>water souchet</asp>.]</altsp> See
<er>Zoutch</er>.⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

